ledEntities(EntityQueryDTO req)` - Query failed entities with pagination\n- `boolean isProcessingFinished(Long entityId)` - Check if processing complete\n- `boolean updateProcessingState(Entity fresh)` - Update processing state\n- `List<Entity> findStuckEntities(Duration staleThreshold, int maxCount)` - Find potentially stuck entities\n- `MarkForReprocessResult markAllForReprocess()` - Mark all entities needing reprocessing\n- `List<Long> findTopNIdsByReprocessState(ReprocessState state, int limit)` - Find IDs by reprocess state\n- `EntityProcessLockInfo findProcessLockInfoById(Long id)` - Get lightweight lock info\n- `boolean claimInitEntityForReprocess(Long id)` - Atomic claim for INIT entity\n- `boolean updateReprocessStateById(Long id, ReprocessState state)` - Update reprocess state\n\n---\n\n### 3. EntityServiceImpl (Implementation)\n**File Path:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/service/EntityServiceImpl.java`\n\n**Class Details:**\n- **Annotations:** `@Slf4j`, `@Service`, `@RequiredArgsConstructor`\n- **Dependencies:**\n  - `EntityRepository` (Spring Data JPA)\n  - `IdService` (qualified as \"IngestionIdService\")\n  - `PlatformTransactionManager`\n  - `MeterRegistry` (Micrometer for metrics)\n\n**Key Implementation Details:**\n- Auto-generates IDs using `idService.nextId()` if null\n- Sets `createdAt` and `updatedAt` timestamps on save\n- Uses `@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)` for interrupt and reprocess state updates (independent transactions)\n- Uses Spring Data JPA `Specification` for dynamic query building (supports filtering by `processingStage`, `processingCode`)\n- Batch processing with transactional guarantees (each batch in separate transaction to prevent long-running txns)\n- Metrics tracking: `policy_reprocess_mark_init_last_failed_batches` (gauge) and `policy_reprocess_mark_init_run_seconds` (timer)\n\n---\n\n### 4. EntityRepository (Interface)\n**File Path:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/repository/EntityRepository.java`\n\n**Extends:** `JpaRepository<Entity, Long>`, `JpaSpecificationExecutor<Entity>`\n\n**Custom Query Methods:**\n- `Optional<Entity> findFirstByTypeAndHostIdentity(EntityType type, String hostIdentity)` - Find by type and host identity\n- `Optional<Entity> findFirstByTypeAndHostIdentityAndUserIdentity(EntityType type, String hostIdentity, String userIdentity)` - Find by type, host, and user identity\n- `int updateInterrupted(Long id, boolean interrupted, Instant updatedAt)` - Update interrupted flag with timestamp\n- `int updateProcessingState(...)` - Update multiple processing fields atomically (interrupted, attributeFingerprint, processingStage, processingCode, lastReqVersion, processingResult, updatedAt)\n- `Page<Entity> findStuckEntities(Instant before, Pageable pageable)` - Find stuck entities (not ENFORCED, no failure code, old updatedAt)\n- `List<Long> findTopNIdsNeedMarkForReprocess(Long lastId, ReprocessState targetState, Pageable pageable)` - Find IDs needing mark\n- `int markBatchForReprocess(List<Long> ids, ReprocessState targetState)` - Batch update reprocess state\n- `List<Long> findTopNIdsByReprocessState(ReprocessState state, Pageable pageable)` - Find IDs by reprocess state\n- `Optional<EntityProcessLockInfo> findProcessLockInfoById(Long id)` - Lightweight projection query\n- `int claimInitEntityForReprocess(Long id, Instant updatedAt)` - Atomic claim: updates INIT → RUNNING\n- `int updateReprocessStateById(Long id, ReprocessState state, Instant updatedAt)` - Update reprocess state\n\n**Important Query Features:**\n- All `@Modifying` queries use `clearAutomatically = true, flushAutomatically = true`\n- Ordered queries for consistent pagination\n- Lightweight projection to avoid loading large columns\n\n---\n\n### 5. Entity (Domain Model)\n**File Path:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/entity/Entity.java`\n\n**Class Annotations:** `@Data`, `@Builder`, `@NoArgsConstructor`, `@AllArgsConstructor`, `@javax.persistence.Entity`, `@Table(name = \"entities\")`\n\n**Fields:**\n- `Long id` - PK, serialized as string via `@JsonSerialize(using = ToStringSerializer.class)`\n- `EntityType type` - ENUM (STRING), not null\n- `String source` - not null, length 20\n- `String userId` - char(36), nullable\n- `String hostId` - char(36), nullable\n- `String adapterId` - char(36), nullable\n- `String userIdentity` - length 255, nullable\n- `String hostIdentity` - length 255, not null\n- `String bindingType` - length 20, nullable\n- `LocalDateTime bindingStartTime` - nullable\n- `LocalDateTime bindingEndTime` - nullable\n- `String processingStage` - length 10, nullable\n- `Integer processingCode` - nullable\n- `String errorMessage` - length 1024, nullable\n- `String processingResult` - LOB (large object), JSON (raw value), nullable\n- `Instant createdAt` - not null\n- `Instant updatedAt` - not null\n- `boolean interrupted` - not null, default false\n- `String attributeFingerprint` - length 255, not null\n- `String lastReqVersion` - length 50, not null\n- `ReprocessState reprocessState` - ENUM (STRING), length 20, not null, default `ReprocessState.NONE`\n\n**Key Annotations:**\n- `@JsonRawValue` on `processingResult` - stores JSON without re-escaping\n- `@Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)` on enums\n\n---\n\n### 6. DTO Classes\n\n#### 6a. EntityStateDisplayDTO\n**File Path:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/dto/EntityStateDisplayDTO.java`\n\n**Fields:**\n- `Long id`\n- `String type`\n- `String hostIdentity`\n- `String userIdentity`\n- `String processingStage`\n- `Integer processingCode`\n- `Instant updatedAt`\n- `String displayStatus` - Values: \"init\", \"running\", \"enforced\", \"failed\", \"unknown\"\n\n**Annotations:** `@Data` (Lombok)\n\n#### 6b. EntityQueryDTO\n**File Path:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/dto/EntityQueryDTO.java`\n\n**Fields:**\n- `String stage` - optional, filtering by `processingStage`\n- `Integer code` - optional, filtering by `processingCode`\n- `Integer pageNum` - default 1\n- `Integer pageSize` - default 10\n- `String sortKey` - options: \"createdAt\" (default), \"processingStage\", \"type\"\n- `String sortOrder` - \"desc\" (default) or \"asc\"\n\n**Annotations:** `@Data`\n\n#### 6c. FingerprintRequestDTO\n**File Path:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/dto/FingerprintRequestDTO.java`\n\n**Fields:**\n- `@NotBlank String entityType` - \"HOST\" or \"USER_HOST_BINDING\"\n- `Long userId` - optional\n- `Long hostId` - optional\n- `Long adapterId` - optional\n- `List<String> userFields` - e.g., [\"email\", \"position\"]\n- `List<String> hostFields` - e.g., [\"os\"]\n- `List<String> dynamicClientFields` - e.g., [\"vendorName\"]\n\n**Annotations:** `@Data`, `@NoArgsConstructor`, `@AllArgsConstructor`, `@Builder`\n\n#### 6d. MarkForReprocessResult\n**File Path:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/dto/MarkForReprocessResult.java`\n\n**Fields:**\n- `int updatedCount` - total rows updated\n- `int failedBatches` - number of failed batches\n- `int failedCount` - total count of entities in failed batches\n\n**Annotations:** `@Data`, `@Builder`, `@NoArgsConstructor`, `@AllArgsConstructor`\n\n#### 6e. MarkForReprocessResponse\n**File Path:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/dto/MarkForReprocessResponse.java`\n\n**Fields:**\n- `int markedCount`\n- `int failedBatches`\n- `int failedCount`\n- `long timeCostMs`\n- `String status` - \"FAILED\", \"PARTIAL_SUCCESS\", \"SUCCESS\"\n- `String message`\n\n---\n\n### 7. Repository Projection\n**File Path:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/repository/projection/EntityProcessLockInfo.java`\n\n**Interface Methods (Lightweight Projection):**\n- `Long getId()`\n- `EntityType getType()`\n- `String getHostId()`\n- `String getAdapterId()`\n- `String getUserId()`\n- `ReprocessState getReprocessState()`\n\n**Purpose:** Avoid loading heavy columns (e.g., `processingResult`) during initial lock checks in reprocess jobs.\n\n---\n\n### 8. Spring Boot Configuration\n\n#### Application Entry Point\n**File Path:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/IngestionApplication.java`\n\n**Annotations:**\n- `@SpringBootApplication(scanBasePackages = \"com.fortinet.nac\")` - Scans entire com.fortinet.nac hierarchy\n- `@EnableAsync` - Enables async execution\n- `@EnableScheduling` - Enables scheduled tasks\n\n#### 8a. IdGeneratorConfig\n**File Path:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/config/IdGeneratorConfig.java`\n\n**Bean:** `ingestionIdGenerator` of type `PersistenceSnowflakeIdGenerator`\n- Uses Snowflake ID generation pattern\n- Configurable: dataCenterId, workerId, dataServerId, intervalSeconds, module, baseDir\n- Default module: 7, baseDir: \"/bsc/campusMgr/config\"\n\n#### 8b. PolicyReprocessAsyncConfig\n**File Path:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/java/com/fortinet/nac/ingestion/config/PolicyReprocessAsyncConfig.java`\n\n**Beans:**\n1. `policyReprocessListenerExecutor` - ThreadPoolTaskExecutor\n   - Default: coreSize=1, maxSize=2, queueCapacity=100, keepAliveSeconds=60\n   - Thread prefix: \"policy-reprocess-listener-\"\n   - RejectedHandler: CallerRunsPolicy\n\n2. `policyReprocessJobExecutor` - ThreadPoolTaskExecutor\n   - Default: coreSize=8, maxSize=16, queueCapacity=32, keepAliveSeconds=60\n   - Thread prefix: \"policy-reprocess-job-\"\n   - RejectedHandler: CallerRunsPolicy\n\n#### Application Configuration (application.yml)\n**File Path:** `/private/tmp/temper-arch/A/ingestion/src/main/resources/application.yml`\n\n**Key Configs:**\n- **Server:** Port 8086\n- **Spring Application Name:** ingestion\n- **Redis:** Redisson with connection pooling (96 max, 24 min-idle), Netty threads=16, Worker threads=8\n- **Database:** MariaDB with JPA, Hibernate dialect, DDL auto=validate\n- **Stream Consumer:** Internal (16 consumers, 32 workers), External (8 consumers, 8 workers)\n- **Ingestion Recovery:** Enabled, staleThreshold=80s, batch-size=2000, rate-limit=100/s\n- **Reactive Thread Pool:** core=30, max=300, queue=10000\n- **Policy Reprocess Job:** scan-interval=30s, batch-size=200, rate-limit=100/s\n- **Metrics:** Prometheus endpoint enabled, histogram distribution for lock-hold time\n\n---\n\n### 9. Package Structure\n```\ncom.fortinet.nac.ingestion\n├── IngestionApplication (main entry point)\n├── bo/\n├── config/\n│   ├── IdGeneratorConfig\n│   ├── PolicyReprocessAsyncConfig\n│   ├── NamedThreadFactory\n│   ├── IngestionRecoveryAsyncConfig\n│   └── NettyOffLoadThreadPoolConfig\n├── controller/\n│   └── EntityController\n├── entity/\n│   └── Entity\n├── service/\n│   ├── EntityService (interface)\n│   ├── EntityServiceImpl (implementation)\n│   └── stages/\n├── repository/\n│   ├── EntityRepository\n│   └── projection/\n│       └── EntityProcessLockInfo\n├── dto/\n│   ├── EntityStateDisplayDTO\n│   ├── EntityQueryDTO\n│   ├── FingerprintRequestDTO\n│   ├── MarkForReprocessResult\n│   └── MarkForReprocessResponse\n├── consumer/\n│   ├── handler/\n│   ├── orchestrator/\n│   ├── recovery/\n│   └── statemachine/\n├── converter/\n├── delayqueue/\n├── exception/\n├── job/\n│   └── event/\n├── registry/\n├── trace/\n└── util/\n```\n\n---\n\n### 10. Key Technology Stack\n- **Framework:** Spring Boot 2.x\n- **ORM:** JPA/Hibernate with MariaDB\n- **Data Access:** Spring Data JPA (Repository pattern)\n- **Caching/Messaging:** Redis with Redisson\n- **ID Generation:** Snowflake-based distributed ID\n- **Async:** Spring Async with ThreadPoolTaskExecutor\n- **Scheduling:** Spring Scheduling\n- **Metrics:** Micrometer/Prometheus\n- **Validation:** Java Bean Validation (javax.validation)\n-